{
  "text": "Considering that neuropathological lesions start 20 years before the onset of clinically symptoms [CITATION_1] , early detection of cognitive decline might be useful to prevent dementia through lifestyle changes and pharmacological interventions [CITATION_2] . Whether adiponectin exerts protective effect on glucose metabolism and neuronal functioning delaying the onset of metabolic and neurodegenerative diseases in middle-aged individuals remains poorly investigated.",
